summary:
I have an MSc in the field of Shipping and Transport, and as well as, I had a bachelor's degree in Marine Engineering - Navigation;

Aside from that, as a professional, I have been a Master Mariner on ocean-going vessels which all of my navigation documents and certificates still valid;

Having 20 years of extensive and transferable maritime industry experience in different sectors;

Possession of Designated Person Ashore (DPA) Certificate on the basis of the ISM Code & IMO Circular (Issued by Korean Register Classification);

Obtain certificates of familiarity with ISO 9001 (2015), ISO 14001 (2015) & ISO 45001 (2018);

I have hands-on experience in dealing with maritime industry codes and regulations, including SOLAS, MARPOL, STCW, IMDG, MLC, ISM, LSA, FSS, and ISPS;

I am an enthusiastic and inspirational professional with global transport and maritime expertise who always:

•	Likes to connect personalities, cultures, beliefs, and possibilities;
•	Looks for opportunities to increase system performance and customer satisfaction;
•	Builds teams that have the individual strength and capability to move forward with organizational solutions;
•	Increases employee efficiency and team performance and overall team satisfaction;
•	Promotes interest in learning new relevant content in teams, and by applying them properly, will improve systems within the organization;
•	Enhances safety and security standards at work;
•	Creates a happy, intimate and vibrant work environment;
•	Are open to ideas, but can also convince people of my ideas;
•	Has strong analytical skills;
•	Enjoys puzzles;

Please contact me at EMAIL to find out how I might contribute and add value to your organization.

profile_positions.description:
Essential Duties: i.a.
•	Involved in the day to day operations of the ship including navigational safety, cargo, ballast and tank cleaning, and inspections;
•	In charge of vessel operations:  optimization of transport capacities regarding booking note, packing lists and vessel stowage plan in coordination with the shipping agent at loading ports and the shipmaster in accordance with instructions given;
•	Implement procedures to improve quality, productivity, and efficiency;
•	Maintaining safety standards and procedures as well as environmental management;
•	Act as a member of an Emergency Response Team;
•	Involved in the analysis and monitoring of operational data to ensure potential problems are averted;
•	Provide guidance to Masters, Fleet Managers, and general management on any special requirements;
•	Attending meetings or sit on committees established within the Maritime industry to represent the company;
•	Provide advice to vessels and fleet management on cargo requirements, tank cleaning, stability and stress and to maintain all statutory requirements for the vessel in this field;
•	Ensuring shipments are delivered in a timely manner;
•	Maintains relationships with carrier vendors and consistently resolves customer issues;
•	Making sure that project/department milestones/goals are met and adhering to approved budgets;

I am eligible to teach marine students such as Officer of the Watch (OOW) >3000gt & <3000gt and sailors on deck, and having experiences to instruct some lessons like Ship Stability, Cargo Work, Chart Work, and Ship Construction and EDH. As well as SOLAS, MARPOL, STCW, MLC and IMDG CODE familiarization courses for officers.

Additionally the above courses, also having the experience to instruct the elements of the following course:

1, Fire Prevention & Fire Fighting;
2, Personal Survival Techniques;
3, Ship Security Officer;
4, Shipboard Safety Officer;
5, Bridge Management Team (BTM);
6, Personal Safety & Social Responsibility;

Achievements: 
- Significant progress for students and a 30% increase in their passing exams. 
- The ability to motivate and encourage students to progress in their studies in an excellent way. 
- To show my commitment, enthusiasm, and skill in this role, depending on the topic, I use my valuable practical experiences at sea during teaching.
- I believe that ''Good teachers never stop learning'', and given that the laws in the marine industry are updated on a daily basis, I have the continuous learning, self-improvement and an instructive attitude in any situation.

•Incharge of the Supply and Logistics operation, covering materials planning, inventory control, rate setting, outsourcing, vendor selection, and distribution. Involved with procurement, customer service, and production/merchandise planning to focus on continuous improvement of products and processes according to customer needs;
•Minimizing total supply chain cost, maximizing supply chain effectiveness including conforming to established quality standards, and establishes an inventory flow that is responsive to the needs of the business;
•Keeping the team informed of promotions, cost advantages, product availability, market trends, vendor and item changes, and related information and anticipate and advise management of potential supply chain problems which may have a significant impact on business;
•Developing and implementing procedures to seek out suppliers that have the best value of the company;
•Performing financial analysis to evaluate make/buy alternatives and lease/buy options and participate in value engineering efforts;
•Developing reports showing transportation costs on precise projects and moves;
•Supporting the maintenance of logistics policies, procedures, support plans, and similar data;
•Providing assistance for maintaining logistics planning tasks;
•Reviewing and analyze program effectiveness, suggest and execute on-time improvements and corrective actions;
•Incharge of the Warehouse, conducting physical cataloging, warehousing, inventorying, material control coordination and data entry assisting different supply activities, investigating inventory divergence, resolve issues and update the database to replicate property movement, establishing and maintaining maximum and minimum consumables inventory levels;
•Administering and maintain inventory control program systems and inventory management programs;
•Developing pertinent schedules, reports and conduct recurring inventories of supplies and property;

BBL Shipping Company is a privately-owned shipping company in Iran, was established in 2013, the member of BIMCO & FIATA, provides professional ship agency, stevedoring operation, project cargo (heavy lift) services, logistics services and chartering the vessel. The number of direct employees in the company in 2017 was 12.

Essential Duties: i.a.

• Maximize earnings of the Operator business unit; 
• Retrieve business opportunities; 
• Responsible for leading the Chartering desk to provide effective and efficient shipping service to the suppliers and customers by obtaining best freights and quality services, same time solving any problems that may arise during the dispatch processor at the customer’s premise;
• Voyage calculations and compare possibilities in accordance with market trends and corporate policies; 
• Making sure shipments are planned according to the agreed schedule & time frame;
• Negotiating charter parties with charterers/operators/brokers; 
• Making charter party details available to operators; 
• Sourcing of single trip and short period tonnage; 
• Developing and maintaining client portfolio; 
• Support the Chartering team in performance control and report;
• Supporting the Senior Commercial Manager;

•	During this period, the team under my direct supervision achieved the following goals:
o	Decrease of 12% in the time the ship stopped at ports and the increased 11% in company revenue from second-year employment, due to saving the entire system; 
o	Delivering the right products to the right location on time and at a good cost; 
o	Considerable improvement of data usage from IT systems to evaluate performance and quality and to plan improvements; 
o	Improve about unify the storage and distribution of goods in worldwide trade;

IRISL was established in 1967, It has 115 ocean-going Vessels, such as container carrier, bulk carrier, the chemical tanker, and multi-purpose carrier. It Provides transportation of containers, bulk cargo (dry & wet), general cargo, supplies fuel, port agent services, ship management, and offshore Services, as well as supplying specialized manpower for ships, etc. The number of employees in the company was over 7,000.

My education:
•	Class 1 (Deck - Master GT>3000 Unlimited);

My responsibilities included: i.a. 
• Acted for and on behalf of the vessel owner, charterer, and cargo owner to protect their interest and keep vessel performance economically feasible;
• Acted on behalf of ship's flag state administration and government to comply with national and international laws;
•  Ensuring  proper  implementation  of  the  Company  Safety  Management  System  (SMS)  and Company  International  Ship  and  Port  facilities  Security  plan  (ISPS)  and  periodical  review  of  the above-mentioned systems as per company procedures;
• Managing of multicultural staff;
• I always managed to create a safe environment on-board, with regards to cargo, vessel, and staff; 
• With foreign authorities, I managed to work and communicate well on a professional basis;
•  Key  achievements:  Elected  as   the  best  National  Mariner  of  2015  in  the  international  day  of seafarers festival held by PSO (Iranian Port and Shipping Organization);

• The ultimate responsibility for securing the safety and security of the ship;
• Assistance to the HSE Director and HSE Manager;
• Conducts regular audits and inspections on-board the vessel;
• Investigate, prepare a report of findings or arrange for all accidents and near-misses;
• Recommendations to prevent recurrence and implement the approved course of action;
• Ensures that all personnel and crew comply with company HSE training and medical requirements; 
• Conduct HSE presentations and training to employees as required;
• Responsible for the effective implementation of company policies with respect to safety, security, and environmental protection;
• Full management of cargo operation including the preparation of cargo plan, loading/unloading, cargo securing (as per ship’s Cargo Securing Manual), and processing relevant cargo documents;
•  Key  achievements:  During  these  years  reasonably,  by  the  team  under  my  direct  supervision, improved safety culture and reach to requirements of the ISM Code, ISPS Code and MLC goals of an  incident-free working environment on-board the ship, and maintained at the correct level;

DKC (Darya Kala Control) Inspection Services Company was established as an Iranian private joint-stock company. The DKC is a commodity and marine advisors and inspectors in different fields such as petroleum, petrochemical products, agricultural products, metals, and marine inspections. The number of direct employees in the company in 2017 was 15.

My activities in this company were as Cargo Surveyor, Bunker Surveyor and Auditor (ISM, ISPS & MLC); 

My responsibilities included: i.a.  

•	Weight calculation of cargo with considered ship stability factors, inspecting the quality of cargo, cargo holds and cargo gear equipment;
•	Inspected for on/off-hire ‘’Bunker Quantity Survey” (BQS) and condition survey;
•	Surveyed vessels for Cargo quantity, Cargo quality, Cargo holds condition and Cargo handling equipment;
•	Carried out inspections of Lifting Appliances General Condition according to relevant international or commercial standards;
•	Audited (Internal and External) the safety management system (SMS), ISM, ISPS, MLC of companies and/or their ships.
•	During this period, our team increased customer satisfaction and reliability by 9% and ship owner satisfaction by an average of 12%;
